Holidays are not available everywhere
In Hungary, days of leave are precisely laid down by law and it has already become a general practice that working days are moving around the holidays, which is less likely to happen next year.
In the European Union and in America, holidays are not uniform.
The Hungarian legal system distinguishes national and state holidays and days of rest.
The days of serenity are usually linked to church holidays or to significant historical events.
We also celebrate New Year with us: the last day of the old and the first day of the new year is work leave - on New Year's Eve so that people can relax after New Year's.
In the course of the year, we have 11 holidays available.
The National Festival is 15 March celebrating the revolution of 1848 and 23 October, the memorial day of the revolution of 1956.
On August 20th, we celebrate the founding of the state, on May 1st work, on November 1st and 2nd we remember the deceased relatives and friends.
Besides, we have two-day Easter, Pentecost and Christmas holidays.
Since our national, national, or religious holidays are rarely for the weekend according to the calendar, it has become a practice to move the day of work in cases where we would only work one day before or after the holiday.
However, the price for extended weekends is that the previous Saturday we stay in the workplace and in school.
The day immediately preceded or followed by the festival will be worked out by the Minister of Labour for many years in a special decree.
The legislation applies equally to all employers and workers employed by them, to public employees and to persons in public service.
However, it does not apply to companies and institutions that are in operation without interruption or, in view of their designation, operate even in the days of rest.
