And in that one of the panels, decomposing like a pulling harmonica, as a result of the snap of the cable, was damaged on an area of nearly one meter.
Decomposition has been suspended to prevent further damage to the panel.
Astronauts, who were originally supposed to perform a control output to the Discovery ship, and then go to repair another solar panel whose rotation system had a malfunction, were forced to deal with the damaged panel.
