He was helped by a second "spacewalker" who remained close to the equalization chamber, and also from within, other astronauts, among them Peggy Witson, commander of the crew.
The tools he used, namely a mini-hockey with an insulation device to prevent electroshock on solar panels producing several hundred volts, invented and "after the DIY" produced astronauts on board the station.
After the operation ended, Scott Parazynski waited until the panel was completely dismantled and then inventoryd his tools and returned to the inner part of the station.
