What kind of insurance is appropriate for me?
The insurance of a car that protects the driver in the event of an accident is a significant expense, which depends on various factors such as age, condition, gender, duration of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle to be insured or used, etc.
Having a car is just the beginning.
Choosing a suitable car insurance is even more difficult than choosing a car model.
First of all, we need to clarify what we're talking about.
Car insurance is an agreement between the insurance company and the insurance company.
This obligation takes the form of an insurance contract which provides that the insurance undertaking receives an agreed premium amount of a certain amount for taking care of the damage in the event of an insurance event.
Insurance is the price of insurance, which is determined by reference to various factors such as age, condition, gender, duration of possession of a driving licence, type of vehicle which is insured or used, etc.
Insurance companies set their prices on the basis of statistics, so the greater the probability of a crash, the higher the insurance rate.
For this reason, both persons over the age of 25 and women must pay lower premiums, as statistics show that they have a lower risk index due to their caution.
In the same way, on the basis of checks, insurance companies concluded that married persons have fewer accidents than free drivers.
The way the vehicle is used will affect the frequency of journeys and thus the probability of having an accident.
The growth in the frequency of rides increases the probability.
There are many variables that insurance companies consider when they determine the price of insurance premiums.
Therefore, the driver must study the situation well in order to choose the insurance which best fits his insurance profile.
We will show here the most important variables for the selection of one or the same type of insurance, which, in addition to complying with the type of insured person, will also be at a reasonable price.
People under the age of 25 face various disadvantages such as the lack of driving experience and the short possession of a driving licence when they want to book insurance premiums at an affordable price.
Although insurance against all risks is ideal for good cover, there are also cheaper options.
The most cautious drivers can choose insurance against all risks with an insurance discount in such a way as to obtain insurance cover for all risks but at a more acceptable price.
This type of contract would assume the participation of the client in the payment of the insurance event.
"Part of the payment of the insurance event provided by the client will be determined in advance in determining the price of the premium, which will be even higher, how much less there would be a contribution", explains Luis Noguera, head of First Europe in Spain, Internet insurance intermediary.
Another option is insurance extended to other traffic participants by insureing the client against damage caused by other persons, but not against damage on his own car.
In addition, it would be insured against theft, fire and loss of vehicle.
Recommendations.
If you are under 25 years of age, try to be attentive and avoid accidents as much as possible, as this will affect your bonus and allow you to reduce your premiums in the future.
The bonus is a reduction of the basic rate that an insurance company has.
On the other hand, malus is an increase in the basic rate.
"Bonus and malus will depend on the insurance company and its profits.
If the insurance company has had a good year, it will be able to afford to raise the bonus," Noguera explains.
After crossing the 25-year limit, drivers have it easier when they go to get insurance, because the client risk index is decreasing, thanks to acquired experience.
For this reason, it is most recommended to arrange insurance against all risks at a discount.
"Young people usually cannot take advantage of the experience gained in advance at the time of the accident and even during the procedure", assures the director of the European company in Spain and adds that most accidents occur in the second year of the procedure, when the "fear of the newcomer" has already been overcome.
However, if the client is married but has no children yet, it is better to arrange insurance against all risks, if his economic situation permits.
Families with children are considered by insurance companies as clients with the lowest risk index and therefore their premiums will be lower.
In this case, the best insurance would be insurance against all risks with an insurance discount (which could be EUR 300) or at a high bonus, insurance extended to other operators, starting from the third year after the purchase of the vehicle.
"Their driving is calmer and their purchasing capacity is higher, so they can afford the luxury of getting the highest discount," said Luis Noguera.
Pensioners are recommended to cover all risks with a premium discount (of EUR 150) or insurance extended to other participants in the operation if a high bonus has been achieved.
It must be said that car insurance is something important not only because it protects drivers in the event of an accident, but also because it represents a significant expenditure, which is a strong reason for appropriate examination of the insurance options that would suit us most in view of our personal situation.
